<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-08T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="1108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1108">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.7962/3–849: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-08T11:00:00+03:00">March
                                        8, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>168. Dhahran’s unnumbered March 7.<note n="1" xml:id="d1108fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> If new <gloss target="#t_DAB1">DAB</gloss>
                                agreement not concluded by March 15 and there seems little prospect
                                as Acting Foreign Minister now Cairo where text proposed new
                                agreement being sent him for comments by Foreign Office, <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> will take initiative in writing
                                Legation on 15th extending present agreement by 15 days. It is
                                Shaikh Yusuf’s view new agreement may be concluded within that <pb facs="1599" n="1583" xml:id="pg_1583"/> time. If it is not
                                    <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> will give further extensions
                                until agreement concluded.<note n="2" xml:id="d1108fn2">The Dhahran
                                    Air Field Agreement was extended 15 days on March 15 (telegram
                                    197, March 15, from Jidda, 890F.7962/3–1549, not printed), and
                                    on subsequent occasions.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>Relayed to Dhahran 40.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>